## 🐛 Bug Report

Between reading in a given xlsx and writing it out, I am seeing the cell and border colours change.

Lib version: 3.0.2

Screenshot of input and output file, as seen in Numbers on macOS X:

<img width="951" alt="Screenshot 2020-04-18 at 19 34 13" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/682269/79673964-a755d680-81ac-11ea-8323-523a498b4f29.png">
<img width="948" alt="Screenshot 2020-04-18 at 19 36 45" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/682269/79673965-a8870380-81ac-11ea-92b1-440215b779ba.png">

## Steps To Reproduce

<!-- The exact steps required to reproduce the issue, ideally with a code example -->

```javascript
async function createExcelSpreadsheet(filePath, data, options: any = {}) {

    const workbook = new Workbook();
    let worksheet;

    if (options.template) {
        const templatePath = './templates/xlsx/my-template.xlsx';
        await workbook.xlsx.readFile(templatePath);
        worksheet = workbook.getWorksheet(1);
    }

    if (!worksheet) {
        worksheet = workbook.addWorksheet('Sheet 1');
    }

    if (options.columns) {
        worksheet.columns = options.columns;
    }

    worksheet.addRows(data);

    await workbook.xlsx.writeFile(filePath);

    return filePath;
}
```

## The expected behaviour:

The styling should not change for unmodified cells, between input and output.


## Possible solution (optional, but very helpful):

```javascript

```

I have attached the two files. Note the initial one was created in Numbers and exported as xlsx. The second was slightly modified to take out data that was not to be shared.

[my-template.xlsx](https://github.com/exceljs/exceljs/files/4498051/my-template.xlsx)
[output.xlsx](https://github.com/exceljs/exceljs/files/4498050/output.xlsx)

